        <strong>Premium Messaging Product Description:</strong>

        <p>
            Widespread use of text (SMS) and multimedia (MMS) messaging has made it an attractive method for brands and
            media
            companies to market to and interact with consumers. Companies that want to market or interact with consumers
            via text
            messaging can set up short codes which serve as addresses to and from which text messages can be sent and
            received.</p>

        <p>
            Verizon Wireless Premium Messaging platform allows content providers to provide VzW Subscribers with access
            to Premium
            Content such as</p>

        <div class="pad">
            <ul>
                <li>Alerts, Jokes, Ringtones, Wallpaper, etc.</li>
                <li>Content delivered <b>via SMS and MMS</b></li>
                <li>Vzw and non-VzW Branded campaigns.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <p>Subscriber Accesses Content via SMS Common Short Code or <b>via Web Store</b></p>

        <div class="pad">
            <ul>
                <li>SMS is addressed to a 5 or 6 Digit Short Code and texts in Keyword of Desired Content within the SMS
                    body.
                </li>
                <li>Content is available via approved web store fronts.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

